Reasoning: The paper deals with the space complexity of refuting random 3-CNFs in Resolution and algebraic systems, which falls under the area of computational complexity theory. The use of Hall's Lemma and the concept of VW-matchings suggest a connection to graph theory and combinatorics, which are also relevant areas in computer science. Therefore, the likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
